During a visit to Brazil, Vice President Mike Pence expressed gratitude for the strong partnership between the United States and Brazil, emphasizing the ties of mutual security, freedom, and economic bonds. He praised Brazil's efforts in strengthening its economy and discussed ways to further encourage commerce between the two countries. Pence also commended Brazil's leadership in addressing the crisis in Venezuela and sought counsel from President Temer on how to continue supporting the Venezuelan people. He expressed his commitment to democracy restoration in Venezuela and mentioned that he and his wife would be meeting with Venezuelan migrants in Brazil. Pence concluded by highlighting the friendship and shared values between Brazil and the United States.